During a visit to King Orchards Market in Central Lake, Michigan, President Biden was asked about the recent hacking incident believed to be carried out by Russians. He stated that they are not certain if it was the Russian government and that he has directed the intelligence community to investigate. He mentioned that if it is determined to be Russia's doing, he will respond accordingly. When asked about Sha'Carri Richardson's temporary ban for marijuana use, the President acknowledged that the rules are the rules, but suggested that the rules themselves could be up for debate. He also commented on the decision to demolish the remaining part of the collapsed tower in Surfside, Florida, stating that he has not been briefed on the reasons behind the decision.